aws cli - Authenticate with AWS and connect with aws cli.

we use IAM to create user swith Adminstrator access and create access key for Authentication to connect to EC2 instance.

enter "aws configure" in EC2 server and give access key and secret key to connect to aws cli.
ls -la and cd .aws and ls -la to check our config and credentials.

aws s3 ls - to verify if we are connected to aws cli successfully.

sed editor:
sed '1a Hi' users - adds Hi after first line temporarily
sed -i '1a Hi' users - adds Hi after first line permanently

sed '1i Hi' users - adds Hi before first line temporarily

sed -i '2d' users - deletes 2nd line permanently

sed '/sbin/d' users - deletes sbin included lines
sed '2s/sbin/SBIN/g' users - replaces sbin with SBIN in 2nd line in all occurrences
sed 's/sbin/SBIN/g' users - replaces sbin with SBIN in all lines in all occurrences


Eg: sh roboshop.sh mongodb catalogue - This is to create ec2 instances for mongodb catalogue and others and update route 53 records for those instances
from roboshop.sh file

Eg: Login to catalogue server and run sudo sh catalogue.sh to execute catalogue.sh script.
Same for other instances such as mongodb, redis etc.

curl http://localhost:8080/health - to check health of catalogue server, it should be {"app":"OK","mongo":false}

tail -50 /var/log/shell-roboshop/mongodb.sh.log - to check logs - $LOGS_FILE of mongodb.sh script file.

